"{\"uid\": \"theargus.co.uk-news-national-uk-today-24484266.paris-olympics-2024-shooting-events-work\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympics 2024Sport  We are now well into the swing of the Paris Olympics 2024 and Team GB are off to a flying start.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 88, \"end\": 95, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9982249697494884, \"rank\": 0.0017777869319472444, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first gold medal for Great Britain at the Olympics was claimed on day three in the\\u00a0team eventing competition for mountain biking and equestrian.\", \"from\": 124, \"to\": 272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 149, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999991660869294, \"rank\": 7.567449789790962e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 261, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9990656998404094, \"rank\": 0.0009040790143871547, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today the men's and women's trap will take place in Paris at 8am for the shooting event.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999984506758, \"rank\": 1.5492536743047439e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But how much do you know about the shooting event?\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Excruciating tension, minute margins and unbreakable concentration - Olympic shooting is a unique challenge.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the original nine Olympic sports, there were only 39 competitors, representing seven different nations in fiveeventsat Athens in 1896.\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 652, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.983024459796673e-14, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport has grown globally since then and the Paris 2024 offering will include 340 competitors vying for 15 gold medals.\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.754318815523202e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic shooting features three types of guns - rifle, pistol and shotgun.\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In rifle and pistol events, athletes shoot at stationary targets at indoor shooting ranges.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shotgun, meanwhile, is held outdoors where shooters have to aim at targets hurled in the air.\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All shooting is done from a set distance of 10m, 25m or 50m, with athletes aiming for a bullseye on a paper target, or flying 'clays' in the shotgun.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rifle: Single-loaded in 5.6-millimetre calibre (the inner diameter of a gun barrel), which is used across all events.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pistol: In the 10m Air Pistol event a single-loaded pistol in 4.5-millimetre calibre is used, whereas the ones used in the 25m events are a Rapid Fire Pistol in 5.6 calibre with a five-shot magazine.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shotgun: A 12 gauge having a calibre of 18.5 millimetres.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The gauge is a unit of measurement for firearms.\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a shotgun, the gauge is determined by the number of equally-weighing spherical balls made from a pound of lead, that can be fit inside the gun barrel.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In rifle shooting, competitors aim at a target with 10 concentric circles from a fixed distance, with two subcategories: 50m Rifle 3 Positions and 10m Air Rifle.\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 50m Rifle 3 Positions, athletes shoot from kneeling, prone, and standing positions, firing 40 shots in each within a two-hour and 45-minute timeframe.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top eight scorers progress to the medal round.\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 10m Air Rifle, participants shoot 60 shots in 75 minutes, and the top eight then compete for medals.\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An elimination format is used for rifle finals, removing the lowest-scoring shooter after each series of shots before gold and silver medals are determined by a head-to-head shoot-off.\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The action continues on Day 4\\ufe0f\\u20e3 of the#Paris2024Olympic Games!\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83c\\udf89\\ud83c\\udfc5Witness incredible performances and unforgettable moments.\", \"from\": 2521, \"to\": 2581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss out!\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\ude80\\ud83d\\udcfahttps://t.co/XeYzw5pd0S#Olympicspic.twitter.com/GfLhTOgvd1  In addition to separate men's and women's events, the 10m Air Rifle includes a mixed team event.\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each team, consisting of one male and one female athlete, fires 40 shots in the qualification round within 50 minutes.\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top five teams advance to the final round.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pistol shooting consists of three subcategories: 25m Rapid Fire Pistol, 25m Pistol, and 10m Air Pistol, all requiring athletes to shoot with one hand only, unsupported.\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 25m Rapid Fire Pistol, exclusively for men, shooters fire successively in short periods of eight, six, and four seconds.\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The qualification round includes two sets of 30 shots each, with the top eight shooters advancing to the medal round.\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 25m Pistol event is exclusive to women and mirrors the format of the 25m Rapid Fire Pistol event, featuring two qualifying rounds of 30 shots each.\", \"from\": 3344, \"to\": 3495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 10m Air Pistol, following the rules of the 10m Air Rifle, there are men's, women's, and mixed team categories.\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the individual categories, shooters fire 60 shots within one hour and 15 minutes, with the top eight advancing to the medal round.\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the mixed team event, each member fires 40 shots, and the top five teams compete for the overall honours.\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3858, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like in rifles, an elimination format is used for pistols, removing the lowest-scoring shooter after each series of shots before gold and silver medals are determined by a head-to-head shoot-off.\", \"from\": 3860, \"to\": 4055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Skeet and Trap are the Olympic shotgun events where athletes shoot at a small, fast-moving target called 'clay,' measuring just 10cm in diameter, and travelling at over 100kph.\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both events include men's and women's categories, while Trap also features a mixed-team event.\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Skeet, male and female athletes shoot at clay targets from eight different stations.\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4340, \"end\": 4345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISSF_Olympic_skeet\", \"score\": 0.9994398876974697, \"rank\": 0.0005604262039355559, \"text\": \"Skeet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISSF_Olympic_skeet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISSF_Olympic_skeet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clays come from the 'high house' on the left and the 'low house' on the right.\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes take 25 shots each in five rounds over three days, with the top six moving on to the medal round.\", \"from\": 4500, \"to\": 4606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Trap, shooters fire at clays thrown from five positions.\", \"from\": 4608, \"to\": 4668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The preliminary round mirrors Skeet for men and women.\", \"from\": 4669, \"to\": 4723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RECOMMENDED READING  In the individual events, the top six go through to a semi-final, with the first two then shooting off for gold and silver and the third and fourth shooting for bronze.\", \"from\": 4725, \"to\": 4914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Trap mixed team event, each shooter fires 75 shots in three rounds, with the top six teams advancing to the medal round.\", \"from\": 4916, \"to\": 5043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Double Trap, releasing two targets simultaneously, has been removed from the Olympic program.\", \"from\": 5045, \"to\": 5142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheNationalShooting Centre in Chateauroux, based approximately 160 miles south of Paris, will host shooting at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5230, \"end\": 5235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999984506758, \"rank\": 1.5492536743047439e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With more than \\u00a330M a week raised for Good Causes, including vital funding into elite and grassroots sport, National Lottery players support our Olympic and Paralympic\\u00a0athletes to\\u00a0live\\u00a0their dreams and make the nation proud, as well as providing more opportunities for people to take part in sport.\", \"from\": 5268, \"to\": 5566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5380, \"end\": 5396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.9997670117352965, \"rank\": 0.0002330397982501401, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To find out more visit:www.lotterygoodcauses.org.uk  This website and associated newspapers adhere to the Independent Press Standards Organisation's     Editors' Code of Practice.\", \"from\": 5568, \"to\": 5747, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you have a complaint about the editorial content which relates to     inaccuracy or intrusion, then pleasecontact the editor here.\", \"from\": 5748, \"to\": 5881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are dissatisfied with the response provided you cancontact IPSO here  \\u00a9 2001-2025.\", \"from\": 5886, \"to\": 5975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Argusis owned and operated by Newsquest Media Group Ltd, an audited local newspaper network.\", \"from\": 5976, \"to\": 6072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6014, \"end\": 6039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsquest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Newsquest Media Group Ltd\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsquest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsquest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Visitnewsquest.co.ukto view ourpoliciesandterms.\", \"from\": 6074, \"to\": 6122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Echo Building, 18 Albert Road, Bournemouth, England BH1 1BZ.\", \"from\": 6124, \"to\": 6188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6128, \"end\": 6136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southern_Daily_Echo\", \"score\": 0.9999988748533687, \"rank\": 1.1251480973685835e-06, \"text\": \"The Echo\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southern_Daily_Echo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southern_Daily_Echo\"}, {\"begin\": 6150, \"end\": 6156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bloom\", \"score\": 0.9994579997282994, \"rank\": 0.000492090890228953, \"text\": \"Albert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bloom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bloom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Registered in England & Wales | 01676637  Data returned from the Piano 'meterActive/meterExpired' callbackevent.\", \"from\": 6189, \"to\": 6301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a subscriber, you are shown80% lessdisplay advertising when reading our                     articles.\", \"from\": 6303, \"to\": 6407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those ads you do see are predominantly fromlocal businessespromotinglocal                         services.\", \"from\": 6409, \"to\": 6516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These adverts enable local businesses to get in front of their target audience - thelocal                         community.\", \"from\": 6518, \"to\": 6642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is important that we continue to promote these adverts as our local businesses need                     as much support as possible during these challenging times.\", \"from\": 6644, \"to\": 6810, \"entities\": []}]}"